description._content: Description: Court House, Victoria, formerly New Oriental Bank, now provides accomodation for the Judge, the Court, the Legal Adviser, the Registrar, the Civil Status Office, the Treasury and Customs Officers and the Auditor. Location: Victoria, Seychelles Date: 1890-1909 Description: Long Chausee on Road from Victoria to Anse Etoile. (In the centre a coral bridge has just been built in place of a dangerous wooden bridge.) Location: Victoria, Seychelles Date: 1890-1909 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/770 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
